[3] Cholera - Sao Tome and Principe (San Tome)
Date: Tue, 8 Oct 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: XinHuaNet.com [edited]
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2005-11/08/content_3752338.htm>

The month-old cholera epidemic in Sao Tome has claimed 9 lives and
struck nearly 300 people, a health official from the West African
archipelago said Tue, 8 Nov 2005.
According to reports, coordinator of the epidemic's emergency team
Manuel Carvalho said 126 new cholera cases and 5 deaths from the
disease had been registered during the past 8 days, raising totals to
292 cases and 9 fatalities.
Carvalho said all districts of Sao Tome Island are affected, but the
outlying island of Principe remains untouched. Authorities have urged
the islanders to avoid using untreated water and uncooked foods and
to destroy garbage and trash.
An earlier epidemic in April affected about 200 people and took 3
lives in the country.
