[4] Cholera - Uganda (Kawempe)
Date: Thu, 10 Nov 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and New Vision (Kampala) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200511100304.html>

The number of people affected with cholera in Katanga is increasing
due to the heavy rains, reports Florence Nakaayi.
During the last 2 weeks, the number of patients admitted to the
cholera camp at Komamboga health center increased from 60 to 144,
with 5 deaths recorded since September, Dr. Joseph Senzoga said. He
said yesterday, 9 Nov 2005, most of the patients were residents of
Kalerwe and Katanga in Kawempe Division. He also said that on
average, 4 to 5 people were being admitted to the center every day,
but added that on Tue, 8 Nov 2005, the number rose to 9. Most of the
affected people live along sewer lines.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
